    <refsection id="Description_CMR_BearingFriction">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This block is a model of Coulomb friction with Stribeck effect in bearings. The output torque, <latex>\tau\:</latex>
            depends on the initial sliding mode.
        </para>
        <para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        If there is a backward initial sliding mode, then:
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <latex>
                            \begin{eqnarray}
                            \tau = Tau\_prop * \omega_{relfric} - Tau\_Coulomb -Tau\_Stribeck * exp(fexp * \omega_{relfric})
                            \end{eqnarray}
                        </latex>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        If there is a forward initial sliding mode, then:
                    </para>
                    <para>
                        <latex>
                            \begin{eqnarray}
                            \tau = Tau\_prop * \omega_{relfric} + Tau\_Coulomb + Tau\_Stribeck * exp(-fexp * \omega_{relfric})
                            \end{eqnarray}
                        </latex>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        If the initial sliding is free, then, <latex>\tau\:</latex> is 0.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        In the last case, <latex>\tau = f(a_{relfric})</latex>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
        <para>
            With, <latex>\omega_{relfric}\:</latex> (resp. <latex>a_{relfric}</latex>) is the relative angular velocity (resp. acceleration)
            between frictional surfaces.
        </para>
    </refsection>
